ofile":{"proxyWallet":"0x8d3036f06df4cae70408efce65d2957245aac338"}},{"id":"2832931","commentID":2874671,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xb57ac09f77d5b726aef74745e951cc7841832ebe","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x8d3036f06df4cae70408efce65d2957245aac338"}},{"id":"2832942","commentID":2874671,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xe640a3efc0c8654d591d7d13c56d4bc3cd8cf884","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x084321c3393d2a3d511ba8118586afe6bd07131e"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":8},{"id":"2874690","body":"Salarymen don't work in factories","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":435295,"parentCommentID":"2874671","userAddress":"0xf4cffacd72d0f5d3e5e66a217b5e5635359bbb41","replyAddress":"0x1184d0edb04ad37fa64fd1db0ef33c2819636db6","createdAt":"2026-05-03T00:18:58.565919Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-03T00:19:05.127423Z","profile":{"name":"1walrus","pseudonym":"Expert-Neuropathologist","displayUsernamePublic":true,"bio":"every turkey has their thanksgiving day","proxyWallet":"0x6560abb717a8e5f3afaacd1a31e9c03eed71e164","baseAddress":"0xf4cffacd72d0f5d3e5e66a217b5e5635359bbb41"},"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":0},{"id":"2874721","body":"My bio is a lie","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":435295,"parentCommentID":"2874671","userAddress":"0x1184d0edb04ad37fa64fd1db0ef33c2819636db6","replyAddress":"0xf4cffacd72d0f5d3e5e66a217b5e5635359bbb41","createdAt":"2026-05-03T00:36:52.344612Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-03T00:36:59.45082Z","profile":{"name":"yen4u","pseudonym":"Key-Sovereignty","displayUsernamePublic":true,"bio":"Just a Japanese salaryman who loves gambling in my spare time.","proxyWallet":"0xf0d5eb1cbe7350f1f896ade6c172e6700414c665","baseAddress":"0x1184d0edb04ad37fa64fd1db0ef33c2819636db6","profileImage":"https://polymarket-upload.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/profile-image-6949826-4cc07b96-61fb-489e-9643-a134dd6a0b50.webp"},"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":0},{"id":"2875261","body":"The market rules clearly state that it resolves to “Yes” if Ruben Rocha Moya “ceases to be the Governor of Sinaloa for any period of time.”\n\nThis condition has objectively been met. The Congress of Sinaloa has officially approved his license, and an interim governor (Yeraldine Bonilla) has assumed the role. During this period, Rocha Moya is not exercising the powers or duties of the office.\n\nThe official communication explicitly states that he has “separated from the position” for a defined period. This directly aligns with the rule language “for any period of time.”\n\nThe interpretation that he “remains the constitutional governor” introduces a legal distinction that is not present in the market rules. The rules do not require permanent removal, resignation, or loss of title — only that he ceases to be governor for any period of time.\n\nIn practice and in governance terms, he has ceased to be governor, as another official is currently exercising executive authority.\n\nTherefore, resolving this market as “No” would contradict the plain meaning of the rules and the observable facts.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":435295,"userAddress":"0x1566ce6ae1325f60f6d4632a0c32ba6bcb4f2dfa","createdAt":"2026-05-03T08:00:01.988961Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-03T08:00:12.023186Z","profile":{"name":"Encimado","pseudonym":"Old-Fashioned-Dialect","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x39aba58bce50b345bb28d93e80a6d992403031f8","baseAddress":"0x1566ce6ae1325f60f6d4632a0c32ba6bcb4f2dfa"},"reactions":[{"id":"2833697","commentID":2875261,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x19501db8416eaf25ba9e60d9bb87489dbf3ed761","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xce4d7123b294829c505302800fc7bc0590b3d0e2"}},{"id":"2833711","commentID":2875261,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xe609fb524b95b21fc488bc3958e0f701ac8e58d8","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x0b652d3e55be0e1d50c2f7be39358585c415293e"}},{"id":"2833759","commentID":2875261,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xc97a69ccd3b3c00957c772f7a145c2955f822880","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x5e55fb0aeb4f585249af2e685fbe070967f34c96"}},{"id":"2833787","commentID":2875261,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xf14a0f5e385d2159e2516bca129c81e6fea3c375","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x1c147f2ecc502e1283e5d51d0352cbc386656342"}},{"id":"2833795","commentID":2875261,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xebbf6de028c90e28038fa3cdf8c34e0dee49a90c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x1edfb719e2502197c4f5a8515bc6154a0d016be6"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":5},{"id":"2873490","body":"Constitución Federal, Artículo 116: Establece que los gobernadores son electos por un periodo de seis años y que su mandato solo termina por conclusión del periodo, revocación de mandato o falta absoluta (muerte, renuncia calificada o destitución por juicio político). Una licencia no se clasifica como \"falta absoluta\".  Federal Constitution, Article 116: Establishes that governors are elected for a six-year term and that their term ends only upon completion of the term, recall, or absolute vacancy (death, qualified resignation, or removal by impeachment). A leave of absence is not classified as an \"absolute vacancy.\"","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":435295,"userAddress":"0x97ff7973342cbd03843b0427f8eec86c151be710","createdAt":"2026-05-02T17:13:14.35508Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-02T17:13:21.247934Z","profile":{"name":"Helldiver15","pseudonym":"Puny-Satisfaction","displayUsernamePublic":true,"bio":"I do analysis for fun and money, Geopolitics/Military Specialist","proxyWallet":"0x7d858550e3f39cb2f605b36e5b068a15bcb63a04","baseAddress":"0x97ff7973342cbd03843b0427f8eec86c151be710","profileImage":"https://polymarket-upload.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/profile-image-4767879-f9f90af8-d3b8-4537-a737-cac6c0965620.png"},"reactions":[{"id":"2832325","commentID":2873490,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x272ae01124eca24bf6e243a32e9419291c33f483","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x0711e162e05349de3d87626dea4285d08537f03c"}},{"id":"2832352","commentID":2873490,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xe640a3efc0c8654d591d7d13c56d4b